  <channel>
    <title>Top 10 Reasons I don't have the best job in the world</title>
    <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=brenlo&amp;message.id=34</link>
    <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;So my last post really got folks talking (some are yelling) and that's a good thing.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Getting folks discussing things is one of the goals I have for this little section.&amp;nbsp; To any who took offense, I apologize as that was most certainly not my intention.&amp;nbsp; Rather it was to stir up some discussion and for many of you it did just that.&amp;nbsp; To clarify one little point, I do understand immersion and I love a truly immersive world.&amp;nbsp; However, immersion should never come at the expense of fun.&amp;nbsp; The first few times you run across an expansive virtual world is a wondrous experience.&amp;nbsp; By the 5th, 6th or 7th time, it starts to become tedium.&amp;nbsp; We have to avoid tedium in a game such as this.&amp;nbsp; People have to be able to get to the fun fast.&amp;nbsp; We also have to maintain that immersion for those folks who do enjoy running across the world, and in most cases we have.&amp;nbsp; The boats are gone for now, and yes even I miss them at times.&amp;nbsp; I remember riding them and exchanging languages or just socializing but when new transport methods were added, I gladly moved on to those and left our old friend the boats behind.&amp;nbsp; Would it be nice to occasionally jump on one and take a trip through the Ocean of Tears?&amp;nbsp; Possibly, on occasion, but that choice is gone and maybe that is why there has been so much talk over some of the changes.&amp;nbsp; That the choice was removed.&amp;nbsp; Like the arena in the bazaar.&amp;nbsp; I think we can all admit that it was seldom used, but the choice was there to use it if you wanted.&amp;nbsp; Something else to discuss I guess.&amp;nbsp; So have at it!&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;So on to the real topic Du Jour.&amp;nbsp; When commuting to work (no not another bad analogy so put down the pitchforks) I have a lot of time to think.&amp;nbsp; This morning while driving in, which only took 25 minutes Yay!, I thought back to all the times over the last 5 years that I have met you folks in person and in particular over this last year that I have been the Community Manager (or in the words of one member&amp;nbsp;of our community, the Court Jester) and many of you fine folk tell me how I must have the best job in the world.&amp;nbsp; While I do have a great job and I enjoy what I do immensely, there are times that it is not so great.&amp;nbsp; They are small things and do not take wholly diminish the overall joy I take in this position, however they deserved mention none the less.&amp;nbsp; So I now present to you the top 10 reasons why being the EQ Community Manager is not the best job in the world.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;#10 - Sharing an office with overly caffeinated Halflings:&amp;nbsp; The Brenlettes (as Lord Pfister calls Ashlanne and Kytherea) are a great asset to the team.&amp;nbsp; They are hard working, dedicated, fun and fond of coffee.&amp;nbsp; It is this fondness that leads to the 10th reason I do not have the best job in the world.&amp;nbsp; When caffeinated these two become a force of nature filled with silliness and creating rampant havoc in my normal daily routine.&amp;nbsp; Whether it be Ashlanne dancing with my chair or Kytherea throwing candy at me, it creates an atmosphere non-conducive to my routine of normality.&amp;nbsp; Now I am certain that these two will now tell that I am far from normal and that I too have a goofy streak but do not believe it for it is just the coffee talking.&amp;nbsp; By the way, Kytherea just made more coffee.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;IMG style="WIDTH: 804px; HEIGHT: 595px" height=859 src="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/images/forum_images/community/Coffee.JPG" width=983&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;#9 - Free Donuts and Bagels on Friday:&amp;nbsp; I know, I know you are thinking what the heck is wrong with Brenlo (and not just because of this list) Donuts, or Doughnuts should be seen as a&amp;nbsp;boon.&amp;nbsp; An enjoyment.&amp;nbsp; A pleasant perk to brighten your day.&amp;nbsp; Each Friday should be relished, even cherished for the grandeur that these pastries bring your morning.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Chocolate covered, jelly filled, maple bars the list goes on and on.&amp;nbsp; Sprinkled, covered in peanuts, old fashioned glazed, how I love the doughnut.&amp;nbsp; However . . . I am on a low carb diet and viewing these tempting and tasty tidbits of carb filled passion and tenderness makes Fridays a&amp;nbsp;little less bright.&amp;nbsp; In a moment of weakness I will even succumb to the sultry and tasty call of the bagel but alas, the Jalapeno bagel is already taken.&amp;nbsp; ARGH!!!&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Look for the countdown to continue tomorrow.&amp;nbsp; And you mongoose conspirators, I am slowly unraveling your secrets.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
