      <title>Re: Top 10 Reasons I don't have the best job in the world</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=brenlo&amp;message.id=35#M35</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Dragons is&amp;nbsp;doing well so far.&amp;nbsp; No major issues and people seem to be having&amp;nbsp;fun with it.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;You&amp;nbsp;folks are still saying&amp;nbsp;good things and we are very happy that you are enjoying it as&amp;nbsp;much as you are.&amp;nbsp; A lot of hours, thought, passion and heart go into these expansions and it is good to see them&amp;nbsp;well recieved (other than some folks have reservations and concerns over the new Bazaar)&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; I am putting up two new threads today that I would encourage you folks to participate in, the first is what do you like most about &lt;A href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Live&amp;amp;message.id=3616" target=_blank&gt;Dragons and Why&lt;/A&gt;,&amp;nbsp; and of course the second is what you enjoy least about &lt;A href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Live&amp;amp;message.id=3617" target=_blank&gt;Dragons and why&lt;/A&gt;.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;So enough of that stuff.&amp;nbsp; The office is quiet for the moment as Kytherea has not made coffee yet and Ashlanne comes in a little later, so I have quiet.&amp;nbsp; Sweet beautiful silence.&amp;nbsp; Even the fish are being quiet for the moment.&amp;nbsp; There are several bettas scattered throughout the office.&amp;nbsp; Kytherea has 2, Ashlanne has 2 and I have one.&amp;nbsp; Kytherea named her fish Mudge and Angel. Not bad, you can tell some thought went into their naming.&amp;nbsp; Ashlanne named her fish Blue and Purple.&amp;nbsp; Bet you can't guess what color they are.&amp;nbsp; Umm yeah.&amp;nbsp; My fish is named Sushi.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Outside of&amp;nbsp;our office is quiet too. Many members of the team are taking some much deserved time off after their hectic launch schedule.&amp;nbsp; These guys work 12+ hour days, 7 days a week for a month of more leading up to the launch.&amp;nbsp; Now they get to unwind a bit.&amp;nbsp; So things are rather relaxed right now.&amp;nbsp; Except for Maddoc who never relaxes.&amp;nbsp; I am not sure he sleeps either, perhaps he is a Design Bot 2000 in reality.&amp;nbsp; I will be really worried if he starts to call me Dave.&amp;nbsp; Those who are here are working on bugs that you folks are pointing out, posting on these forums or working hard to add to my already fragile sanity state.&amp;nbsp; Curse you Zarillius!&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Anywho I imagine you came to see number 7 and 8 or perhaps to see if Brenlo has finally lost it?&amp;nbsp; I assure you I lost it long ago. . .&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;8 - Acronyms:&amp;nbsp; Acronyms in EQ have gone crazy.&amp;nbsp; You folks are acronym masters, creating abreviated versions of phrases, spells, skills, zones, games, companies, our expansions and some even overlap.&amp;nbsp; SOE Nerfed SOE!&amp;nbsp; Huh?&amp;nbsp; FBM, IBTL, IIRC, CIHYS, SOW, SSoY, POK, XYZ PDQ!&amp;nbsp; Soon you will all be speaking in acronyms and have to use accents to determine which version of the acronym you mean,&amp;nbsp;"Dang! SOE' really should reevalute S'OE."&amp;nbsp; I know typing is teh loss, but all of these acronyms are enough to make a short halfling take a long walk of a deep water pier (don't dare me I will, but I know a secret. . .&amp;nbsp; I can swim)&amp;nbsp; We need an acronym to English dictionary in here some days as the three of us look at each in other in confusion ( not our normal confused Halfling looks as we ponder where to get our next&amp;nbsp;installment of Mocha Pie but real confusion like&amp;nbsp;the kind a man gets when he has to change a diaper for the first time)&amp;nbsp;and wonder what Skippy the Ranger was trying to say in 18 letters or less.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;7&amp;nbsp;-&amp;nbsp;The&amp;nbsp;Incredible Disappearing&amp;nbsp;Pfister:&amp;nbsp; Our Executive Producer&amp;nbsp;is a lot of fun to work for and with.&amp;nbsp; He&amp;nbsp;leads&amp;nbsp;and treats us&amp;nbsp;well and I would&amp;nbsp;dare to say that we all have a fondness for the man.&amp;nbsp; However,&amp;nbsp;I think&amp;nbsp;he is a super hero&amp;nbsp;or&amp;nbsp;perhaps the world's greatest magician in his off hours (which are few as he is usually the first one here and the last to leave, with the exception of Maddoc who never leaves).&amp;nbsp; He has the power to vanish.&amp;nbsp; Right into thin air.&amp;nbsp; He has even&amp;nbsp;done it in front of me mid sentence.&amp;nbsp; Houdini, Svengali,&amp;nbsp;Lance Burton have nothing on Robert.&amp;nbsp; He&amp;nbsp;doesn't even need a cabinet to&amp;nbsp;vanish like some of these so called prestigitators.&amp;nbsp; He disappears like&amp;nbsp;the wind, leaving only his laughter behind.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; It is truly an amazing sight to behold.&amp;nbsp; Perhaps he has a secret invisibility formula or moves faster than the eye can see.&amp;nbsp; Who knows!&amp;nbsp; Someday I will unravel his secrets though, that's a promise.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; At least we know he's not a Cleric.&amp;nbsp; (Sorry Clerics, I couldn't resist.)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Look for reasons 6 and 5 soon.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
