      <title>Re: Top 10 Reasons I don't have the best job in the world</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=brenlo&amp;message.id=36#M36</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;What a good start to a day.&amp;nbsp; Ashlanne intervened and made sure that I got the jalapeno bagel!&amp;nbsp; Yes!&amp;nbsp; I finally got my spicy, tasty, chewy morning snack.&amp;nbsp; Mmmmm.&amp;nbsp; Now if only I had my jalapeno jelly to put on it.&amp;nbsp; I make my own and I am especially careful to keep my foot hair out of the canning process.&amp;nbsp; If you have not tried jalapeno jelly, I suggest you do.&amp;nbsp; Put some over some cream cheese and serve with crackers.&amp;nbsp; Very tasty and for those of you afraid of a little spice, it actually does not have much of a kick, just a lot of flavor.&amp;nbsp; I think that Tunare had me in mind when she created jalapenos.&amp;nbsp; I love those things.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Thursdays and Fridays are not so bad to begin with.&amp;nbsp; I carpool on those days so the occasionally long tedium becomes a lot more enjoyable.&amp;nbsp; Today's commute was pretty quick which was good, as I started Ashlanne with a cup of coffee when she picked me up and a halfling on caffeine talks faster than a Californian drives.&amp;nbsp; Of course today she bragged that she has now pulled way ahead of me in quests in EQ2.&amp;nbsp; I have not been playing much as I have been engrossed in DoN and that show on Sci Fi, the 4400.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; So I will let her have her brief shining moment of superiority and then I will crush her.&amp;nbsp; I wonder if the GMs can add completed quests to my total?&amp;nbsp; Just kidding.&amp;nbsp; (No really, any EQ2 GMs that read this give me a call.&amp;nbsp; I have some jalapeno jelly with your name on it.&amp;nbsp;) &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Ashlanne is consuming her third cup of coffee this morning.&amp;nbsp; Not a standard mug mind you but travel mugs.&amp;nbsp; The day may have started well but is about to get a little wild.&amp;nbsp; Batten down those hatches folks, a caffeine storm is on the way.&amp;nbsp; If they are already battened down, batten them down again, we'll teach those hatches.&amp;nbsp; (gotta love Bugs Bunny)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;So onto the continuing drama that is the top 10 reasons I don't have the best job in the world.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;6 - Halfling Envy:&amp;nbsp; All Halflings know how great we are.&amp;nbsp; It is engrained within us from our earliest days in Rivervale.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Halflings are the best at nearly everything.&amp;nbsp; The only thing that springs to mind that we are not best at is being ugly.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Trolls have that one tied up forever I should think.&amp;nbsp; So we know we are the bestest and so do the rest of you.&amp;nbsp; That's why you have to make so many halfling jokes to boost your own inferior egos.&amp;nbsp; We are smarter, cuter, faster, more agile, better public speakers, have better foot hair, romantic, great bakers, the best cooks, lovers and life and you are all just jealous.&amp;nbsp; It's okay to be jealous but please stop the lashing out.&amp;nbsp; You only do yourselves a disservice by insulting us.&amp;nbsp; You cannot dent our perfect personas with your feeble attempts at insultery, such as "Halflings taste good with ketchup"&amp;nbsp; Come now, even baby halflings can do better than that.&amp;nbsp; Even the term @$$ling is tainted with your envy of our fine posteriors.&amp;nbsp; Yes, each time you scream that term at us, we are reminded of how great we fill out our breeches.&amp;nbsp; Do yourselves a favor and accept that we are the bomb.&amp;nbsp; Halflings are Teh Win.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;5 - Lucy:&amp;nbsp; Not Lucille Ball, she is great.&amp;nbsp; "Oh Ricky!"&amp;nbsp; Her and the candy on the conveyor belt.&amp;nbsp; Classic comedy (Yes Halflings know comedy).&amp;nbsp; I mean that program that reports any change made to the game the minute it shows up on Test.&amp;nbsp; I cannot tell you how many times (I use that phrase alot) someone has complained to me about a spell/aa/discipline they saw on Lucy, that never makes it live, yet they tell me they were nerfed.&amp;nbsp; How can you be nerfed when the spell/aa/discipline never existed outside of Lucy?&amp;nbsp; Nerf implies taking functionality away that you had.&amp;nbsp; In the case of many changes on Lucy they never existed.&amp;nbsp; One of the worst cases of Lucymania is when an expansion is in beta and the first round of potential spells is sniffed out.&amp;nbsp; Oh the complaints begin in great volume over spells that are still being tweaked and modified.&amp;nbsp; They are &amp;nbsp;torn apart, parced, compared, evaluated and dismissed before they ever see the light of day.&amp;nbsp; Sending valuable feedback is one thing, we appreciate it and value it.&amp;nbsp; Many things are changed due to your feedback believe it or not.&amp;nbsp; However, &lt;EM&gt;this spell sucks &lt;/EM&gt;does little to help us.&amp;nbsp; Now we really do enjoy that people go to all the trouble to make tools like this.&amp;nbsp; It shows the passion they have for this little world we all share, all I ask is to keep the information in context please.&amp;nbsp; Pretty please?&amp;nbsp; With jalapeno jelly on top?&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;So I will end this all with a quick note on passion.&amp;nbsp; We know you love this game and this world.&amp;nbsp; We know that you have inexhaustible amounts of passionate feelings for the game and its creators.&amp;nbsp; I love to see that passion when I talk with you about this game and our company.&amp;nbsp; It reminds me of why I am here.&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Remember that we are equally as passionate about the game.&amp;nbsp; This is not some hamburger that we fry, dress, wrap up and toss to the customer.&amp;nbsp; This is a labor of passion.&amp;nbsp; Nearly everyone on this team came to the company because of this game.&amp;nbsp; We were all players first.&amp;nbsp; We make a game that we want to play too.&amp;nbsp; We are proud of what we do even when we make mistakes and sometimes we do.&amp;nbsp; When you talk to us, remember that we share your passion.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Our passion simply takes a different form.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Thanks folks for all you contribute to Norrath.&amp;nbsp; Our shared little corner of virtual reality.&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;p&gt;Message Edited by Brenlo on &lt;span class=date_text&gt;02-25-2005&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=time_text&gt;11:38 AM&lt;/span&gt;</description>
