&lt;DIV&gt;U2.&amp;nbsp; Love that band.&amp;nbsp; More the older stuff than the newer.&amp;nbsp; In the Name of Love has to be one of the best songs ever.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Early morning April 4&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;shot rings out in the Memphis sky&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Free at last they took your life&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;They could not take your pride. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Wow.&amp;nbsp; Anyway I bet you cannot guess who I was listening to on my drive in today?&amp;nbsp; So for the hour it took to get to work this morning, I listened to U2 and I got to thinking about The Edge.&amp;nbsp; How cool is that to be called The Edge all your professional career?&amp;nbsp; Urban legend has it that the band called him that as they felt he gave them an edge over other bands.&amp;nbsp; I wonder if it ever gave him a big head?&amp;nbsp; I think perhaps we should tag some of our folks with names likes this, maybe some of our Lead Designers like Jason "Sticky Buns" Mash cause he holds it all together or John "The Calculator" Troy cause he is a master of number crunching?&amp;nbsp; Oooh what about Chris "Rock Solid" Lena&amp;nbsp; for his tight schedules or Cory "Animaster" Rohlfs for his character work?&amp;nbsp; U2 will be here in concert soon and unfortunately I will not be going, they are sold out.&amp;nbsp; It's sad really, I was hoping to pick their minds for some other cool names for our team.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;So on to numbers 4 and 3&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;4 - Children:&amp;nbsp; Now I know what you are thinking.&amp;nbsp; That Brenlo hates kids and that is far from the truth.&amp;nbsp; I love the way kids see the world before all of us cynics open them up to the realities of life.&amp;nbsp; Kids are great, magical little creatures that we could all learn a great deal from; how to share without concern, how to love without boundaries.&amp;nbsp; The world needs more kids.&amp;nbsp; No, I am talking about all of my red-headed step children.&amp;nbsp; Apparently I have thousands and possibly millions.&amp;nbsp; Rangers, Druids, Magicians, each class has claimed to be my red headed step child at least once.&amp;nbsp; Pvpers, roleplayers, newbies, raiders, casuals in fact some of you are linked to me as step children through several different relationships.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;As a ranger, pvper, casual player does that make you three times my stepchild? &amp;nbsp; I do find it statistically impossible that all of you have red hair.&amp;nbsp; I am also quite sure that I have never harmed any of you although I am quite often accused of smacking you.&amp;nbsp; I must admit that I am a bit overwhelmed to have so many step children dependant upon me.&amp;nbsp; How am I going to feed you all?&amp;nbsp; I refuse to do TV commercials,"Please send your generous donation to Feed Brenlo's Step Children."&amp;nbsp; The Class you save could be the one you play next."&amp;nbsp; While I stand&amp;nbsp;casually by eating&amp;nbsp;a pork chop sandwich.&amp;nbsp; (Go Joe).&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Just remember that Papa Brenlo loves all his step children equally and no you cannot borrow the car this weekend.&amp;nbsp; Get your own.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;3 - San Diego Traffic:&amp;nbsp; Living in San Diego has many perks.&amp;nbsp; Beaches nearby, mountains nearby, Disneyland, Seaworld.&amp;nbsp; You almost always know what the weather will be like.&amp;nbsp; Not much smog.&amp;nbsp; Lots to see and do.&amp;nbsp; And unfortunately lots of traffic. I know I have touched on this before and you know all about my daily traffic woes.&amp;nbsp; Let me share some more with you.&amp;nbsp; This morning it took me 30 minutes, to travel 3 miles to get ON the freeway.&amp;nbsp; No accidents, no mishaps no construction (other than the seemingly endless road construction that has been underway since I moved here 5 years ago) Just lots and lots and lots and lots of people.&amp;nbsp; Did I mention there were lots of people?&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Going to lunch each day usually means traffic.&amp;nbsp; Have to go to the airport?&amp;nbsp; Add 45 minutes to your travel time.&amp;nbsp; I suppose that I should just add more time to everything I plan to do that involved using the roadways, like going out to dinner or seeing a movie.&amp;nbsp; But NOOOO. . . Each time I am caught offguard again by traffic.&amp;nbsp; The movie starts in 30 minutes, the theater is less than 5 miles away.&amp;nbsp; Plenty of time!&amp;nbsp; Not in San Diego. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Anyway see you again soon with more of my shenanigans.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
